	(472,'paigebmullaney@gmail.com','mailymurray@yahoo.com',1067,'2015-05-11 05:07:42','Reply: Hello!','Hi Paige,\r\n\r\nI can definitely help you search for many scholarships available to college students. It does take time from you and work on your part to fill out the applications, write essays, poems, art work....or what is needed to apply to a scholarship. What I can help you with is: find a variety of scholarships so you won&#39;t be bored with just writing essays, give you all the information needed to apply to a scholarship, give you deadlines for submissions and review your essays before you submit to give you additional ideas to make it &#34;great&#34;. Some scholarships take minutes to apply to online, some may take a couple of hours to write an essay and submit it online, and some scholarships want you to mail your application. I have a list of questions that you can answer that will help me search for scholarships. Take a look at it and answer as much as possible with as much detail as possible and let me know if it&#39;s something you want me to help you with. my fee is $125 per hour and I can work  as many hours as you need--I can work 1 hour, 2 hours, etc. \r\n\r\nScholarship search questionnaire:\r\n1. List your high school, elementary and middle schools and the cities they are in. (some schools offer scholarships to alumni). What college are you currently attending and what year are you in?\r\n2. List all clubs you are a member of. List all positions you held in those clubs. Did you receive any awards or commendations? What leadership role did you have?\r\n3. Are you a member of Reserve Officer Training Corps? What is your rank? Did you have any leadership role ROTC? Did you receive any awards or commendations?\r\n4. List all classes and grades you received. Did you receive any awards or commendations?\r\n5. List foreign language classes and your grades. Did you receive any awards or commendations?\r\n6. List fieldtrips overseas you’ve taken and why were you there? Did you volunteer while overseas?\r\n7. are you a member of the band? What instruments do you play and any leadership role? Did you receive any awards or commendations?\r\n8. do you play sports, position and leadership role? Did you receive any awards or commendations?\r\n9. any Volunteering? Where and what did you do? What leadership role did you have?  For example, did you set up a food drive? Did you receive any awards or commendations?\r\n10. Girl Scouts or Boy Scouts? What level did you achieve? What major volunteering and leadership role did you have in these organizations? Did you receive any awards or commendations? Did you become an Eagle Scout? Did you receive your Gold Award?\r\n11. GPA, any awards or commendations for your academic achievement?\r\n12. Do you play any instrument outside of school? Did you receive any awards or commendations? Concerts you participated in? Recitals or music exams you took outside of school? Do you teach or have you taught anyone to play an instrument? Did you participate in any county, state, local or regional festivals or competitions?\r\n13. What is your major or what are you interested in doing after college?\r\n14. Religious affiliation? What leadership role did you have? Did you receive any awards or commendations?\r\n15. Do you have a job? What type of job are you doing? How many hours per week do you work while attending school? Did you receive any awards or commendations? What leadership role at work did you have?\r\n16. Did you start any clubs? What leadership role did you have?\r\n17. List all martial arts skill and accomplishments.\r\n18. Do you have any “hidden” talents?\r\n19. List anything that may “set” you apart from other applicants.\r\n20. Where do you see yourself in 5 years?\r\n21. What adversities have you overcome?\r\n22. How do you plan to use the scholarship money? You should come up with a budget that spells out all estimated college expenses and how you will pay for college(they like