	(908,'mglibuit01@gmail.com','mosam@inbox.com',21,'2015-06-04 13:51:26','Reply: Reply: Student with ADHD/borderline Autism in Queen Creek','Not yet.  Here is the text of the original email I received from my friend:\r\n\r\nEssentially, I&#39;m seeking Special Ed. advice and I thought I&#39;d consult an expert.\r\n \r\nI have an old friend who lives in queen creek with his wife and two children.  They have an eight year old son who has ADHD and borderline autism. the mother home schooled him last year but would prefer a school for his socialization. He is at least of average intelligence.  They have not been able to  find a good public school.  The private schools are not eager to take him because such kids require extra time.\r\n\r\nI suspect that Queen Creek is too far for you to teach or tutor. \r\n\r\nMy Dad told me that the teachers at Phoenix Hebrew Academy were very good with kids like this.  The parents are not jewish.  They probably can afford private tuition.  They are resigned to the cost.\r\n\r\nSo the questions are:\r\n1.  Do you have any interest in tutoring?\r\n2.  If not, do you know of any capable tutors on the east side who would be interested in such a student.\r\n3.  Are there any Jewish schools on the east side of the valley that would (1)  take a non-jewish student given the issues listed above; and (2)  Are the east valley jewish elementary schools any good or equipped to deal with such issues?   \r\n\r\nAnd here is my reply to him so far:\r\n\r\nI doubt that Phoenix Hebrew Academy would actually work for  him, especially since there is no religio-cultural reason for him to be in a Jewish school.  And I must agree that Queen Creek is further than I want to commute.  May I shoot this question to some associates who might possibly know someone out that way? \r\n\r\n\r\nI just got to thinking a little bit.  On the &#34;what do we do as homeschoolers for socialization&#34; question:\r\nHave they looked at:\r\nhttp://homeschool.meetup.com/cities/us/az/queen_creek/\r\nhttp://www.home-school.com/groups/AZ.html\r\nhttp://www.afhe.org/support_groups_maricopa_county.html\r\n?\r\n\r\nAnd... on the teaching side, how did last year go?  Are they able to handle the curriculum?  Are there areas where they feel ill-equipped to teach him?\r\n\r\nI haven&#39;t gotten answers on that yet,\r\n\r\nMaurice',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'inbox',903),
