ments attract more parents and students!\r\n  \r\n    Be sure to include the following in your Personal Statement: \r\n•	Your prior tutoring experience (if any)\r\n•	Your skills and qualifications\r\n•	Your teaching style & philosophy\r\n•	Examples of positive results your students have achieved\r\n\r\nExample Short Description/Personal Statement:\r\n________________________________________________________________________________________\r\nTest Prep Specialist—SAT, ACT, GRE, & GMAT\r\nI am a highly qualified tutor with over five years of experience helping students achieve their goals. I specialize in test prep, including the PSAT, SAT, ACT, GRE, and GMAT. I also tutor junior high and high school students in Math (Pre-Algebra, Algebra I, and Geometry) and foreign languages, including Spanish levels 1 through 5 & AP Spanish, beginning French, and beginning German. \r\n\r\nI have a bachelor’s degree in Spanish and extensive experience working as a tutor. My career as a tutor started when I received training in test preparation with a private tutoring company where I worked for two years. Since then, I have continued to tutor independently and have guided many students through their test preparation process for both college entrance exams and AP exams. I provide not just tips and tricks to ace the SAT and other exams, but also share the comprehensive content knowledge necessary to excel on these exams.\r\nI customize and adapt my lessons to meet the unique needs of each individual student. I develop a rapport with each of my students, meeting them where they are and helping them to excel. My patience and enthusiasm for the subjects I teach create a positive environment in which real learning happens.\r\n\r\nI work mainly with junior high and high school students (PSAT, SAT, ACT, and academics), and adult learners (GRE, GMAT, TOEFL, and ESL). My familiarity with multiple languages, such as Spanish, French, and German (in addition to my native English) helps me relate to the unique challenges of learning and studying in a foreign language. \r\n____________________________________________________________________________\r\nI hope you find these suggestions helpful! If you have any questions, comments, or concerns, please do not hesitate to reach out to us. We are here to support you every step of the way!\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nAshlynn Kindschy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'inbox',NULL),
